<strong>no red</strong>
<link rel="help" href="http://www.w3.org/TR/css-flexbox-1/#flex-wrap-property">
<p>Test passes if there is a filled green square and <link rel="help" href="http://www.w3.org/TR/css-flexbox-1/#flex-direction">, the number within square is '1 128 3 4'
  from left to right, top to bottom.</p>
<meta name="assert" content="The 'flex-flow' property set 'row wrap' controls the flex container is multi-line">
<style>
  #test {
    background-color: red;
    display: flex;
    flex-flow: row wrap;
    height: 100px;
    width: 100px;
  }
  #test div {
    background-color: green;
    height: 50px;
    width: 50px;
  }
</style>
<body>
  <link rel="match" href="flex-flow-002-ref.html">
  <div id="test">
    <div>1</div>
    <div>2</div>
    <div>3</div><div>3</div><div>3</div>
    <div>4</div>
  </div>
</body>
